        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001/11–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-30T19:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TelCan 777. Re Cantel 1300 Nov 25 and 1312 Nov 29. Pls arrange to see Li
                    Tsung-jen as soon as possible and state, as under instrs from ur Govt, that
                    reports have come to us that Pres Li might resign during his visit to US, and
                    that if resignation shld be or become his intention it is our desire that it be
                    carried out either prior or subsequent to his trip and not while he is in US.
                    You shld point out his resignation while in this country wld inevitably be
                    interpreted as instigated or inspired by US Govt, an interpretation which this
                    Govt definitely does not wish to be made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
